MALARIA - JAMAICA (KINGSTON): REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: 4 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Radio Jamaica [edited]
<http://www.radiojamaica.com/news/story.php?category=2&story=30639>

Mr. McKenzie, who met with Opposition Leader Bruce Golding Monday
morning to discuss the situation, says while the community has
responded positively to the malaria alert, there is a need for closer
collaboration with the Health Ministry. And despite the reported
increase in the number of Malaria cases that has been brought to the
attention of medical authorities, the Health Ministry is insisting
that it has the matter under control.
According to the Ministry, there are now 13 confirmed malaria cases
which are all confined to the Kingston 12, 13 and 14 areas. Thirteen
cases have been discovered in Delacree Park, Denham Town, Trench Town
and Tivoli Gardens. Five children are among the 13 persons diagnosed
with the insect-borne disease.
The Ministry says the children have been hospitalised, but none is
considered to be critical. Several persons suspected to have
contracted the disease are also in health facilities. Despite this,
Team Leader Dr. Marion Bullock-Ducasse says there is no need for alarm.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
